HEADWORD: Gossan
<hw>Gos"san</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>Decomposed rock, usually reddish or ferruginous (owing to oxidized
pyrites), forming the upper part of a metallic vein. Called also
<altname>iron hat</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gossaniferous</ent>⟦br⟧
